Note.Content: MT פָּקַד, but should probably be read as פֹּקֵד

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = state in which an object or event is either absent or non-existant
= state in which an object is non-existent, implying that it has been destroyed, or that it exists in people's imagination only; ≈ regarded therefore as totally insignificant
= marker indicating that a certain event would occur but was finally avoided

= referent to an unknown location; ► normally used with the purpose of finding out from which location a person or object originates; ≈ sometimes used in rhetorical questions expressing one's conviction that that location does not exist
